theme

Current "theme" string

theme

ValidationRules

The validation rules object. This contains all base rules for validation that come bundled as part of Soho. These rules can be extended.

new ValidationRules()

SCROLLACTION_DEFAULTS

Default ScrollAction Options

SCROLLACTION_DEFAULTS

disable

Make elements in the jQuery selector disabled if they support the prop disabled. Or has a disable method.

disable(): Array<jQuery>
Returns
Array<jQuery>: processed, jQuery-wrapped elements

bindFirst

Used for changing the stacking order of jQuery events. This is needed to override certain Events invoked by other plugins http://stackoverflow.com/questions/2360655

bindFirst(name: string, fn: function): void
Parameters
name (string) the event name
fn (function) callback function that will be called during the supplied event name
Returns
void:

enable

Make elements in the jQuery selector enabled if they support the prop disabled. Or has a enable method.

enable(): Array<jQuery>
Returns
Array<jQuery>: processed, jQuery-wrapped elements

uniqueId

Generates a unique ID for an element based on the element's configuration, any Soho components that are generated against it, and provided prefixes/suffixes.

uniqueId(className: string?, prefix: string?, suffix: string?): string
Parameters
className (string?) CSS classname (will be interpreted automatically if it's not provided)
prefix (string?) optional prefix
suffix (string?) optional suffix
Returns
string: the compiled uniqueID

readonly

Make elements in the jQuery selector readonly if they support the prop readonly. Or has a readonly method.

readonly(): Array<jQuery>
Returns
Array<jQuery>: processed, jQuery-wrapped elements

cssPropSupport

Detect whether or not a text string represents a valid CSS property. This check includes an attempt at checking for vendor-prefixed versions of the CSS property provided.

cssPropSupport(prop: string): (string | null)
Parameters

Accordion

The Accordion is a grouped set of collapsible panels used to navigate sections of related content. Each panel consists of two levels: the top level identifies the category or section header, and the second level provides the associated options.

new Accordion(element: object, settings: object?)
Parameters
element (object) The component element.
settings (object?) The component settings.
Name Description
settings.allowOnePane string (default true) If set to true, allows only one pane of the Accordion to be open at a time. If an Accordion pane is open, and that pane contains sub-headers only one of the pane's sub-headers can be open at a time. (default true)
settings.displayChevron string (default true) Displays a "Chevron" icon that sits off to the right-most side of a top-level accordion header. Used in place of an Expander (+/-) if enabled.
settings.rerouteOnLinkClick string (default true) Can be set to false if routing is externally handled
settings.source boolean (default null) A callback function that when implemented provided a call back for "ajax loading" of tab contents on open.

Dropdown

Parameters

Name Description
settings.closeOnSelect boolean (default true) When an option is selected, the list will close if set to "true". List stays open if "false".

settings.filterMode string (default 'contains') Search mode to use between 'startsWith' and 'contains', false will not allow client side filter

settings.source boolean? A function that can do an ajax call.
settings.sourceArguments boolean (default {}) If a source method is defined, this flexible object can be passed into the source method, and augmented with parameters specific to the implementation.
settings.reloadSourceOnOpen boolean (default false) If set to true, will always perform an ajax call whenever the list is opened. If false, the first AJAX call's results are cached.
settings.empty boolean (default false) Initialize Empty Value
settings.delay boolean (default 300) Typing buffer delay in ms
settings.maxWidth number (default null) If set the width of the dropdown is limited to this pixel width. Fx 300 for the 300 px size fields. Default is size of the largest data.
settings.placementOpts object (default null) Gets passed to this control's Place behavior

Datagrid

The Datagrid Component displays and process data in tabular format.

new Datagrid(element: (Array<jQuery> | HTMLElement), settings: object?)
Parameters
element ((Array<jQuery> | HTMLElement)) The component element.
settings (object?) The component settings.
Name Description
settings.actionableMode boolean (default false) If actionableMode is "true, tab and shift tab behave like left and right arrow key, if the cell is editable it goes in and out of edit mode. F2 - toggles actionableMode "true" and "false"
settings.cellNavigation boolean (default true) If cellNavigation is "false, will show border around whole row on focus
settings.rowNavigation boolean (default true) If rowNavigation is "false, will NOT show border around the row
settings.alternateRowShading boolean (default false) Sets shading for readonly grids
settings.columns array (default []) An array of columns (see column options)
settings.dataset array (default []) An array of data objects
settings.columnReorder boolean (default false) Allow Column reorder
settings.saveColumns boolean (default false) Save Column Reorder and resize
settings.saveUserSettings object (default {columns:true,rowHeight:true,sortOrder:true,pagesize:true,activePage:true,filter:true}) Save one or all of the following to local storage
settings.editable boolean (default false) Enable editing in the grid, requires column editors.
settings.isList boolean (default false) Makes the grid have readonly "list" styling
settings.menuId string (default null) ID of the menu to use for a row level right click context menu
settings.menuSelected string (default null) Callback for the grid level context menu
settings.menuBeforeOpen string (default null) Callback for the grid level beforeopen menu event
settings.headerMenuId string (default null) Id of the menu to use for a header right click context menu
settings.headerMenuSelected string (default false) Callback for the header level context menu
settings.headerMenuBeforeOpen string (default false) Callback for the header level beforeopen menu event
settings.uniqueId string (default null) Unique ID to use as local storage reference and internal variable names
settings.rowHeight string (default normal) Controls the height of the rows / number visible rows. May be (short, medium or normal)
settings.selectable string (default false) Controls the selection Mode this may be: false, 'single' or 'multiple' or 'mixed' or 'siblings'
settings.groupable object (default null) Controls fields to use for data grouping Use Data grouping, e.g. {fields: ['incidentId'], supressRow: true, aggregator: 'list', aggregatorOptions: ['unitName1']}
settings.spacerColumn boolean (default false) if true and the grid is not wide enough to fit the last column will get filled with an empty spacer column.
settings.stretchColumn boolean (default 'last') If 'last' the last column will stretch we will add more options.
settings.clickToSelect boolean (default true) Controls if using a selection mode if you can click the rows to select
settings.toolbar object (default false) Toggles and appends toolbar features fx..
settings.selectChildren Boolean (default true) Can prevent selecting of all child nodes on multiselect {title: 'Data Grid Header Title', results: true, keywordFilter: true, filter: true, rowHeight: true, views: true}
settings.initializeToolbar boolean (default true) Set to false if you will initialize the toolbar yourself
settings.paging boolean (default false) Enable paging mode
settings.pagesize number (default 25) Number of rows per page
settings.pagesizes array (default [10,25,50,75]) Array of page sizes to show in the page size dropdown.
settings.indeterminate boolean (default false) Disable the ability to go to a specific page when paging.
settings.source Function (default false) Callback function for paging
settings.hidePagerOnOnePage boolean (default false) If true, hides the pager if there's only one page worth of results.
settings.filterable boolean (default false) Enable Column Filtering, This will require column filterTypes as well.
settings.disableClientFilter boolean (default false) Disable Filter Logic client side and let your server do it
settings.disableClientSort boolean (default false) Disable Sort Logic client side and let your server do it
settings.resultsText string (default null) Can provide a custom function to adjust results text on the toolbar
settings.showFilterTotal boolean (default true) Paging results display filter count, change to false to not show filtered count
settings.rowReorder boolean (default false) If set you can reorder rows. Requires rowReorder formatter
settings.showDirty boolean (default false) If true the dirty indicator will be shown on the rows
settings.showSelectAllCheckBox boolean (default true) Allow to hide the checkbox header (true to show, false to hide)
settings.allowOneExpandedRow boolean (default true) Controls if you cna expand more than one expandable row.
settings.enableTooltips boolean (default false) Process tooltip logic at a cost of performance
settings.disableRowDeactivation boolean (default false) if a row is activated the user should not be able to deactivate it by clicking on the activated row
settings.sizeColumnsEqually boolean (default false) If true make all the columns equal width
settings.expandableRow boolean (default false) If true we append an expandable row area without the rowTemplate feature being needed.
settings.redrawOnResize boolean (default false) If set to false we skip redraw logic on the resize of the page.
settings.exportConvertNegative boolean (default false) If set to true export data with trailing negative signs moved in front.
settings.columnGroups array (default null) An array of columns to use for grouped column headers.
settings.treeGrid boolean (default false) If true a tree grid is expected so addition calculations will be used to calculate of the row children
settings.onPostRenderCell Function (default null) A call back function that will fire and send you the cell container and related information for any cells cells with a component attribute in the column definition.
settings.onDestroyCell Function (default null) A call back that goes along with onPostRenderCel and will fire when this cell is destroyed and you need noification of that.
settings.onEditCell Function (default null) A callback that fires when a cell is edited, the editor object is passed in to the function
settings.onExpandRow Function (default null) A callback function that fires when expanding rows. To be used when expandableRow is true. The function gets eventData about the row and grid and a response function callback. Call the response function with markup to append and delay opening the row.
settings.emptyMessage object (default {title:'No Data Available',infor:'',icon:'icon-empty-no-data'}) An empty message will be displayed when there is no rows in the grid. This accepts an object of the form emptyMessage: {title: 'No Data Available', info: 'Make a selection on the list above to see results', icon: 'icon-empty-no-data', button: {text: 'xxx', click: }} set this to null for no message or will default to 'No Data Found with an icon.'

Bar

A bar chart or bar graph is a chart or graph that presents categorical data with rectangular bars with heights or lengths proportional to the values that they represent. This is adapated from http://jsfiddle.net/datashaman/rBfy5/2/

new Bar(element: string, settings: string?)
Parameters
element (string) The plugin element for the constuctor
settings (string?) The settings element.
Name Description
settings.dataset array (default []) The data to use in the line/area/bubble.
settings.isStacked boolean (default true) Default is a single or stacked chart.
settings.isNormalized boolean (default false) If true its a 100% bar chart
settings.isGrouped boolean (default false) If true its a grouped bar chart
settings.showLegend boolean (default true) If false the legend will not be shown.
settings.animate (boolean | string) (default true) true|false - will do or not do the animation, 'initial' will do only first time the animation.
settings.redrawOnResize boolean (default true) If true, the component will not resize when resizing the page.
settings.formatterString string? Use d3 format some examples can be found on http://bit.ly/1IKVhHh
settings.format string (default true) The d3 axis format
settings.tooltip string (default null) A tooltip for the whole chart
settings.useLogScale boolean (default false) If true log scale is enabled.
settings.ticks object (default null) Settings for the chart ticks. Can set ticks: {format: d3Format, number: n}
settings.showLines boolean (default true) Show the in the axis lines or not.
settings.labelFactor number (default 1.27) How far out than the outer circle should the labels be placed, this may be useful to adjust for some labels.
settings.wrapWidth number (default 60) The number of pixels after which a label needs to be given a new line. You may want to change this based on label data.
settings.emptyMessage object (default { title:(Locale?Locale.translate('NoData'):'No Data Available'), info:'', icon:'icon-empty-no-data'}) An empty message will be displayed when there is no chart data. This accepts an object of the form emptyMessage: {title: 'No Data Available', info: 'Make a selection on the list above to see results' icon: 'icon-empty-no-data', button: {text: 'xxx', click: <function>} } Set this to null for no message or will default to 'No Data Found with an icon.'

Toolbar

The Toolbar Component manages various levels of application navigation. It contains a group of buttons that functionally related content. Each panel consists of two levels: the top level identifies the category or section header, and the second level provides the associated options.

    Component Default Settings

    TABS_DEFAULTS
    Properties
    addTabButton (boolean) : If set to true, creates a button at the end of the tab list that can be used to add an empty tab and panel
    addTabButtonCallback ((null | function)) : if defined as a function, will be used in-place of the default Tab Adding method
    appMenuTrigger (boolean) : If set to true, will force an App Menu trigger to be present on Non-Vertical Tabs implementatations.
    appMenuTriggerText (string) : If defined, replaces the default "Menu" text used in the app menu trigger.
    ajaxOptions ((null | object)) : if defined, will be used by any internal Tabs AJAX calls as the desired request settings.
    beforeActivate ((undefined | function)) : If defined as a function, fires this before a tab is activated to allow a possible "veto" of the tab swap (SOHO-5250).
    containerElement ((null | string | Array<jQuery>)) : Defines a separate element to be used for containing the tab panels. Defaults to a .tab-panel-container element that is created if it doesn't already exist.
    changeTabOnHashChange (boolean) : If true, will change the selected tab on invocation based on the URL that exists after the hash.
    hashChangeCallback ((null | function)) : If defined as a function, provides an external method for adjusting the current page hash used by these tabs.
    lazyLoad (boolean) : if true, when using full URLs in tab HREFs, or when using Ajax calls, tabs will be loaded as needed instead of the markup all being established at once.
    moduleTabsTooltips (boolean) : if true, will display a tooltip on Module Tabs with cut-off text content.
    source ((null | function)) : If defined, will serve as a way of pulling in external content to fill tabs.
    sourceArguments (object) : If a source method is defined, this flexible object can be passed into the source method, and augmented with parameters specific to the implementation.
    tabCounts (boolean) : If true, Displays a modifiable count above each tab.
    verticalResponsive (boolean) : If Vertical Tabs & true, will automatically switch to Horizontal Tabs on smaller breakpoints.

    RADAR_DEFAULTS

    RADAR_DEFAULTS
    Properties
    dataset (array) : The data to use in the radar

    levels (number) : How many levels or inner circles should there be drawn.
    maxValue (number) : What is the value that the biggest circle will represent
    labelFactor (number) : How far out than the outer circle should the labels be placed, this may be useful to adjust for some charts.
    wrapWidth (number) : The number of pixels after which a label needs to be given a new line. You may want to change this based on label data.
    • @property {boolean} showCrosslines Set to false to hide the cross line axes.
    showAxisLabels (boolean) : Set to false to hide percent labels.
    opacityArea (number) : The opacity value of the blobs. This is set to the correct Infor Style.
    dotRadius (number) : The size of the colored circles of each blog. Set to zero to remove dots.
    opacityCircles (number) : The opacity of the circles of each blob 0 or .1 are good values. This is set to the correct Infor Style.
    strokeWidth (number) : The width of the stroke around each blob. This is set to the correct Infor Style.
    roundStrokes (boolean) : If true the area and stroke will follow a round path (cardinal-closed).
    showCrosslines (boolean) : If false the axis lines will not be shown in the diagonals.
    showAxisLabels (boolean) : If false the axis labels will not be shown.
    axisFormatter (string) : D3 formatter to use on the axis labels
    colors (array) : An array of colors to use.
    showTooltips (boolean) : If false no tooltips will be shown.
    tooltip (object) : A setting that controls the tooltip values and format.
    • tooltip.show string

      Controls what is visible in the tooltip, this can be value, label or percent or custom function.

    • tooltip.formatter object

      The d3.formatter string.

    showLegend (boolean) : If false the legend will not be shown.
    legendPlacement (string) : Where to locate the legend. This can be bottom or right at the moment.
    emptyMessage (object) : An empty message will be displayed when there is no chart data. This accepts an object of the form emptyMessage: {title: 'No Data Available', info: 'Make a selection on the list above to see results', icon: 'icon-empty-no-data', button: {text: 'xxx', click: <function>} } Set this to null for no message or will default to 'No Data Found with an icon.'

    Line

    A line chart or line graph is a type of chart which displays information as a series of data points called 'markers' connected by straight line segments.

    new Line(element: string, settings: string?)
    Parameters
    element (string) The plugin element for the constuctor
    settings (string?) The settings element.
    Name Description
    settings.dataset array (default []) The data to use in the line/area/bubble.
    settings.tooltip (function | string)? A custom tooltip or tooltip renderer function for the whole chart.
    settings.isArea string? Render as an area chart.
    settings.isBubble string (default false) Render as a bubble chart.
    settings.showLegend string (default true) If false the label will not be shown.
    settings.xAxis object? A series of options for the xAxis
    settings.xAxis.rotate number? Rotate the elements on the x axis. Recommend -65 deg but this can be tweaked depending on look.
    settings.xAxis.ticks object? Data to control the number of ticks and y axis format. For example {number: 5, format: ',.1s'} would show only 5 yaxis points and format the data to show 1K, 1M, 1G ect.. This uses the d3 formatter.
    settings.xAxis.formatText function? A function that passes the text element and a counter. You can return a formatted svg markup element to replace the current element. For example you could use tspans to wrap the strings or color them.
    settings.yAxis object? A series of options for the yAxis
    settings.yAxis.formatter function? A d3 formatter for the yAxis points.
    settings.yAxis object? A series of options for the yAxis
    settings.hideDots boolean (default false) If true no dots are shown
    settings.axisLabels array? Option to a label to one of the four sides. For Example {left: 'Left axis label', top: 'Top axis label', right: 'Right axis label', bottom: 'Bottom axis label'}
    settings.animate (boolean | string)? true|false - will do or not do the animation. 'initial' will do only first time the animation.
    settings.redrawOnResize boolean (default true) If true, the component will not resize when resizing the page.
    settings.dots object? Option to customize the dot behavior. You can set the dot size (radius), the size on hover and stroke or even add a custom class. Example dots: { radius: 3, radiusOnHover: 4, strokeWidth: 0, class: 'custom-dots'}
    settings.formatterString string? Use d3 format some examples can be found on http://bit.ly/1IKVhHh
    settings.emptyMessage object? An empty message will be displayed when there is no chart data. This accepts an object of the form emptyMessage: {title: 'No Data Available', info: 'Make a selection on the list above to see results', icon: 'icon-empty-no-data', button: {text: 'xxx', click: <function>} } Set this to null for no message or will default to 'No Data Found with an icon.'

    DatePicker

    A component to support date entry.

    new DatePicker(element: (Array<jQuery> | HTMLElement), settings: object?)
    Parameters
    element ((Array<jQuery> | HTMLElement)) The component element.
    settings (object?) The component settings.
    Name Description
    settings.showTime boolean (default false) If true the time selector will be shown.
    settings.timeFormat string? Format to use time section fx HH:mm, defaults current locale settings.
    settings.minuteInterval number?
    settings.secondInterval number?
    settings.mode string? Time picker options: 'standard', 'range', this controls the time picker.
    settings.roundToInterval boolean? In time picker mode, if a non-matching minutes value is entered, rounds the minutes value to the nearest interval when the field is blurred.
    settings.dateFormat string (default 'locale') Defaults to current locale but can be
    settings.placeholder string (default false) Text to show in input element while empty.
    settings.disable object? Disable dates in various ways. For example {minDate: 'M/d/yyyy', maxDate: 'M/d/yyyy'} . Dates should be in format M/d/yyyy or be a Date() object or string that can be converted to a date with new Date().
    settings.disable.dates array? Disable specific dates. Example {dates: ['12/31/2018', '01/01/2019'} .
    settings.disable.minDate (string | date)? Disable up to a minimum date. Example {minDate: '12/31/2016'} .
    settings.disable.maxDate (string | date)? Disable up to a maximum date. Example {minDate: '12/31/2019'} .
    settings.disable.dayOfWeek array? Disable a specific of days of the week 0-6. Example {dayOfWeek: [0,6]} .
    settings.disable.isEnable boolean (default false) Inverse the disable settings. If true all the disable settings will be enabled and the rest will be disabled. So you can inverse the settings. For example if you have more non specific dates to disable then enable ect.
    settings.showLegend boolean (default false) If true a legend is show to associate dates.
    settings.customValidation boolean (default false) If true the internal validation is disabled.
    settings.showMonthYearPicker boolean (default false) If true the month and year will render as dropdowns.
    settings.hideDays boolean (default false) If true the days portion of the calendar will be hidden. Usefull for Month/Year only formats.
    settings.advanceMonths number (default 5) The number of months in each direction to show in the dropdown for months (when initially opening)
    settings.legend array? Legend Build up for example [{name: 'Public Holiday', color: '#76B051', dates: []}, {name: 'Weekends', color: '#EFA836', dayOfWeek: []}]
    settings.range object? Range between two dates with various options.
    settings.range.useRange boolean (default false) Use range of two dates options.
    settings.range.start (string | date)? Start date in range.
    settings.range.end (string | date)? End date in range.
    settings.range.separator string (default ' - ') Visual separator between two dates.
    settings.range.minDays number (default 0) Minimum days to be in range.
    settings.range.maxDays number (default 0) Maximum days to be in range.
    settings.range.selectForward boolean (default false) Range only in forward direction.
    settings.range.selectBackward boolean (default false) Range only in backward direction.
    settings.range.includeDisabled boolean (default false) Include disable dates in range of dates.
    settings.calendarName string? The name of the calendar to use in instance of multiple calendars. At this time only ar-SA and ar-EG locales have either 'gregorian' or 'islamic-umalqura' as valid values.
    settings.useUTC boolean (default false) If true the dates will use UTC format. This is only partially implemented https://jira.infor.com/browse/SOHO-3437

    Autocomplete

    The Autocomplete control provides an easier means of searching through a large amount of data by filtering down the results based on keyboard input from the user.

    new Autocomplete(element: object, settings: object?, boolean: any)
    Parameters
    element (object) The component element.
    settings (object?) The component settings.
    Name Description
    settings.source string (default []) Defines the data to use, must be specified.
    settings.sourceArguments string (default {}) If a source method is defined, this flexible object can be passed into the source method, and augmented with parameters specific to the implementation.
    settings.filterMode string (default 'startsWith') The matching algorithm, startsWith and contains are supported - false will not filter client side
    settings.delay boolean (default 300) The delay between key strokes on the keypad before it thinks you stopped typing
    settings.width string (default null) Width of the open auto complete menu
    settings.offset string (default null) For the open menu, the left or top offset
    settings.autoSelectFirstItem string (default false) Whether or not to select he first item in the list to be selected
    settings.resultsCallback function? If defined, does not produce the results of the Autocomplete inside a popupmenu, instead piping them to a process defined inside this callback function.
    settings.highlightMatchedText boolean (default true) The highlightMatchText property.
    settings.highlightCallback function? The highlightCallback property.
    settings.resultIteratorCallback function? The resultIteratorCallback property.
    settings.displayResultsCallback function? The displayResultsCallback property.
    settings.searchableTextCallback function? The searchableTextCallback property.
    boolean (any) If defined, use this to draw the contents of each search result instead of the default draw routine.

    Overrides a similar method in the popupmenu code that controls escaping of this menu when pressing certain keys.
